0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__articlePage","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BlogPosting\",\"headline\":\"Expert Tips: Preparing Your Deck for a Virginia Summer\",\"image\":[\"https://www.ldndecks.com/images/img01.jpeg\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-04-17T04:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-04-17T04:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks Team\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\"}],\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"Loudoun Decks\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/ldndecks-logo.webp\"}},\"description\":\"Summer is around the corner! Follow our professional checklist to ensure your outdoor space is safe, clean, and ready for BBQ season.\",\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://www.ldndecks.com/blog/preparing-deck-for-virginia-summer\"},\"isAccessibleForFree\":true,\"inLanguage\":\"en-US\",\"speakable\":{\"@type\":\"SpeakableSpecification\",\"cssSelector\":[\".leadParagraph\",\"h1\",\"h2\"]}}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgWrapper","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"src":"/images/img01.jpeg","alt":"Expert Tips: Preparing Your Deck for a Virginia Summer","fill":true,"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__heroImg","priority":true,"sizes":"100vw"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__imgOverlay","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerLarge","children":[["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__backLink","children":"← Back to News"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__title","children":"Expert Tips: Preparing Your Deck for a Virginia Summer"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__meta","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__author","children":["By ","Loudoun Decks Team"]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__divider","children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"April 17, 2026"}]]}]]}]}]]}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentSection","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__containerNarrow","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__contentBody","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__leadParagraph","children":"Summer is around the corner! Follow our professional checklist to ensure your outdoor space is safe, clean, and ready for BBQ season."}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"With the Virginia humidity and intense summer sun fast approaching, now is the perfect time to give your deck the attention it deserves. A proactive afternoon of maintenance can prevent costly repairs later in the season and ensure your family has a safe haven for summer gatherings."}],["$","h2","1",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"1. The Deep Visual Inspection"}],["$","p","2",{"children":"Before the first BBQ of the season, walk your deck with a critical eye. Check for loose boards, protruding nails, or wobbly railing posts. In Loudoun County, the freeze-thaw cycles of winter can often loosen ledger board bolts or cause wooden posts to check and split. If you notice structural movement when leaning against the railing, it is time to call a professional for a safety certification."}],["$","h2","3",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"2. The Great Spring Wash"}],["$","p","4",{"children":"Winter leaves behind more than just dirt; it leaves a film of algae and fungal spores that thrive in the coming humidity. \n- **For Wood Decks:** Use a dedicated wood cleaner and a soft-bristle brush. Avoid high-pressure settings that can \"fuzz\" the wood fibers.\n- **For Composite Decks:** Use warm, soapy water and a soft cloth or brush to remove sticky pollen and mold spores. This simple step keeps your Trex or TimberTech boards looking vibrant."}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8"],"$L9"]}]}]}],"$La"]}],["$Lb"],"$Lc"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"Jebrcr4Vyd2YosxlccnHN"}
4:["$","h2","5",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"3. Sand and Seal (If Necessary)"}]
5:["$","p","6",{"children":"If you have a natural wood deck and notice that water no longer beads on the surface, your sealant has failed. April is the ideal window for restaining, as the temperatures are moderate and the humidity is lower than in July. Sanding down the rough spots and applying a fresh UV-inhibiting stain will protect your wood from the brutal mid-day sun."}]
6:["$","h2","7",{"style":{"marginTop":"40px","marginBottom":"20px","color":"#111"},"children":"4. Lighting and Electrical Check"}]
7:["$","p","8",{"children":"Test your integrated deck lighting. Replace any burnt-out LEDs in your stair risers or post caps. Ensure your GFCI outlets are functioning correctly—you don’t want your outdoor kitchen or string lights failing in the middle of a Fourth of July party!"}]
8:["$","p","9",{"children":"By following this simple checklist, you ensure your deck remains the highlight of your home all summer long. Need a hand with a professional deep clean or structural repair? The Loudoun Decks team is here to help."}]
9:["$","div",null,{"className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__conclusionBox","children":[["$","h3",null,{"children":"Ready to upgrade your outdoor living space?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Contact Loudoun Decks today for a free estimate and planning consultation."}],["$","$L3",null,{"href":"/contact","className":"BlogContent-module__WEG1wW__ctaBtn","children":"Get Started"}]]}]
